         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>214</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... erlöst d[ies]er vorgetragene edle Weg die Wesen (vom) Bösen ...</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... this proclaimed, noble way redeems the beings (of) evil ...</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>507</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1958a"/><citedRange>148</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1959"/><citedRange>253</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>117</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>134</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1968"/><citedRange>218</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>113</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>134</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1959"/><citedRange>253</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">through ... the three evils/contaminations disappear, through ... the four [bodily] entanglements are cut off. 18. ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... schwinden die drei Unreinheiten.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... the three impurities fade.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>113</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... durch ... schwinden die drei Befleckungen, durch die ... werden die vier [körperlichen] Verstrickungen beseitigt [wtl. abgeschnitten].</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... through ... the three blemishes disappear, through the ... the four [physical] entanglements are eliminated [lit. cut off].</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>209</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1983"/><citedRange>16</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">A being that desires happiness (obtains happiness) if he acts accordingly: …’</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">A being that desires happiness (obtains happiness) if he acts accordingly: …</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>648</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>210</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b7"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>124</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1954"/><citedRange>743</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>43, 46, 64, 71, 95</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... das gute Gesetz [Akk.!], würdig, auf dem Scheitel getragen zu werden.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... the good law [acc!], worthy of being worn on the crown of the head.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>366</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
